main event: Two farmers spotted a bright white light in the sky that suddenly broke up into numerous smaller lights, which then moved across the sky.
interesting points: The bright white light was initially mistaken for the planet Venus, but then rapidly broke up into 8-12 smaller lights that faded in and out.
The cluster of lights moved across the sky in a straight line from an elevation of 35 degrees to 20 degrees.
The farmers had been plowing a field at night when they noticed the initial bright light.
One of the farmers had a long-standing interest in astronomy and recognized the planet Venus.
The farmers reported hearing a low humming sound associated with the sighting.
sighted object: cluster of bright white lights in the sky
photographs: no, the report does not mention any photographs
